  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/noria/ontology/ActionPostCondition">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/noria/ontology/ProceduralObject"/>
    <rdfs:label>ActionPostCondition</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Set of Post Conditions or Potential outcomes that the execution of some OperationPlan may satisfy/lead to/confirm/solve.

From the *ChangeRequest* perspective this enables to declare what to observe in order to confirm that the Procedure reached its goal; from the *TroubleTicket* perspective this enables to capitalize on expectations and outcomes for a given Procedure.</rdfs:comment>
    <skos:example>In an Incident Management context, the materialization to expect, such as:
- 'service restored',
- 'traffic down',
- 'Customer or a probe with that traffic coming up after some CLI command'.</skos:example>
    <vs:term_status>unstable</vs:term_status>
