  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/noria/ontology/Resource">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label>Resource</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">General resource record of the Communication Device kind from the logistics park. It is a managed entity that can be either Physical or Virtual.

Alignment:
- *SEAS*: Whenever a Resource individual is an assembly of other resources (e.g. a server rack) or is part of an assembly (e.g. a server blade), the Resource individual can also be declared as a `seas:System` in order to benefit of the `seas:subSystemOf` relation.
  For example, Resources may be grouped in some `noria:Service` class for providing both an end-to-end analysis of the data path (i.e. Communication Devices + Connections) and an abstract object linked to some end user (e.g. Customer).
- *BOT*: A `noria:Resource` is a sub-class of `bot:Element` for setting instances in the context of a physical environment (e.g. in a building).
- *SLOGERT*: A `noria:Resource` is equivalent to a `log:Host`.
- *UCO*: A `noria:Resource` is equivalent to an UCO's observable `Device`.
</rdfs:comment>
    <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">ICT resource.</skos:altLabel>
    <skos:altLabel xml:lang="fr">Elément structurant informatique et télécoms.</skos:altLabel>
    <rdfs:seeAlso rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/noria/kos/Resource/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/noria/ontology/StructuralElement"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/seas/System"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/seas/CommunicationDevice"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/bot#Element"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://unifiedcyberontology.org/ontology/uco/observable#Device"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/sepses/ns/log#Host"/>
    <vs:term_status>stable</vs:term_status>
    <skos:changeNote>Changes in v0.2:
- Adding rdfs:subClassOf bot:Element.
- Adding rdfs:subClassOf observable:Device.
- Adding rdfs:subClassOf log:Host.
</skos:changeNote>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/noria/ontology/"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/noria/ontology/ApplicationModuleCRMProd">
